**Abstract:** Essay analyzing Aquinas's view of Holy Scripture and its role in sacred doctrine. Argues that while Aquinas acknowledges Scripture as the foundation of theology, his Aristotelian methodology leads him to treat biblical texts as sources for propositional truths rather than as narratives with their own integrity. Shows how the scientific model of theology systematically ignores the narrative character of Scripture.
